<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n05019c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n05" href="#n05019c">N05 (VI.B.2)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n05all.htm#n05019c"> 19(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> gecko</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">We may here observe that many animals in the Bible menagerie are wrongly ticketed, especially those in the eleventh of Leviticus. The eagle should be the vulture, the vulture the kite, the kite the red kite, the owl the ostrich, the nighthawk the owl, the cuckoo the gull, the ferret the <mark>gecko</mark>, the chameleon the frog, the mole the chameleon, the bittern the porcupine, the swan the ibis, and the heron the grasshopper. <small> G.W. Foote, <a name="BROM" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#BROM"><cite title="source">Bible Romances</cite></a>, 4th ed. (1922) [Bible Animals] 157</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: A type of lizard, the gecko is noted for its eerie cry and its agility in scaling walls. </mm> </dd></dl>
